58.5	James_Truslow_Adams	James Truslow Adams	James Truslow Adams (October 18, 1878 â€“ May 18, 1949) was an American writer and historian. He was not related to the famous Adams family (though he wrote a book about the family in 1930). He was not an academic, but a freelance author who helped to popularize the latest scholarship about American history and his three volume history of New England is well regarded by scholars.	
